race.comment: MIND OVER MATTER (5) was making his debut for the new barn and scored a 4.5-length maiden win. Can only be fitter after having six months off and should be racing through the grades this area on that effort. SUPID DATE (11) is going better than form suggests, the latest in 3yo grade here when seventh over much further. Back in trip and back in class and should improve sharply. COPPABELLA ROAD (3) just missed two back and was thereabouts latest. Best form stacks up and worth another chance. TORERA (13) last appeared on November 11 when a good sixth over 1100m at Mackay, beaten 2 lengths. Placed 2/4 fresh and looks a key runner. STATESWOMAN (10) returns from a let-up after a narrow miss at Cairns latest. Will be winding up late.
